âœ… What is a Cooling Zone (in DC Track / Network context)?

You can explain it like this (simple + accurate):

> A Cooling Zone represents the logical area (room/space) where cooling is applied and managed as a group, not an individual CRAC unit.

The sensible capacity at the cooling zone level represents the total effective cooling available to that room/zone, regardless of how many CRAC/CRAH units feed it.



